> "Have you heard about the anti-virus software PC Medic by Pure
> Technology ?  Pure Technology claims that PC Medic can protect against
> ALL (!!!) current and future viruses because it uses a new technology
> - - not signature scanning or CRC.

Well, I have no information on the particular product mentioned, but I
am working in the virus field since four years, and all my experience
tells me that the above claim is completely bogus. There is NO WAY to
protect a PC against all current and future viruses, and still leave
it usable. The nearest thing is to have a system with no writable
media, with all software pre-installed (and guaranteed virus-free).
Under no conditions should you write-enable any of the disk drives
(including the floppies) of such system. It will stop all viruses, but
I doubt very much that many people will find such a system useful.

