Date:    Wed, 28 Oct 92 11:16:35 +0000
From:    Jim.Moore@ericom.ericsson.se
Subject: Re: cascade virus info wanted. (PC)

Hi Lachlan,

There are 3 variants of Cascade and they all infect .COM files only.

The virus replaces the first 3 bytes of the .com file is replaced by a
jump to the start of the virus, which is encrypted bar the first 35
bytes using an algorithm that includes the length of the host program
( so every example 'appears' different ).  It loads as a TSR when the
.com is run and will infect EVERY .com file run, even if it has an
.exe extension.  The 3rd version of cascade has been modified to
format the hard-disk using the routine from the DataCrime virus.

Length of versions:  1 = 1701, 2 & 3 = 1704.

Note: Recognition of the virus depends upon it's length therefore it
      will re-infect .com files that are already infected with cascade
      variants.

Good luck,  Jim.

