>F-Prot 2-05a to remove the infection but all I'm getting is this
<...rest of message deleted...>

The Cansu or V-Sign virus is a floppy disk boot sector and hard disk
master boot record (partition table) infector.  You should be able to
remove it with the DOS SYS command from floppies and MS-DOS 5.00 FDISK
command with the undocumented /MBR switch, which refreshes the MBR
code while leaving the data portion--the actual partition
table--intact.  Alternatively, CLEAN-UP V97 will remove it with the
[Cansu] I.D. code.

