Date:    Tue, 20 Oct 92 13:04:00 -0400
From:    Rudy Hehn <rudy.hehn%hombas@canrem.uucp>
Subject: HELP! (RE: IBM PASSWORD) (PC)

- -> A student has installed some form of password protection on the
- -> machine.  If you boot from a floppy disk, the machine hangs.  If you
- -> boot from the hard-drive, the screen clears and the word 'Password:'
- -> is displayed.

The AMI and DTK BIOS, as well as some others, have this option, which
I always warn people not to use. The only way to delete a forgotten
password is to take off the system cover and, depending on the make of
the motherboard, either disconnect the battery (if it's external)
and/or find the proper jumper pins and short them out to wipe out the
data.  Consult your manual to find out what your system requires. It's
usually recommended not to short the pins out for more than 10
seconds.

