Hello Nikolaj,

In article <0018.9210271550.AA18013@barnabas.cert.org> you write:
>I recently got the McFee Scanv97 for Windows.  I'm running OS/2, but
>when I want to run WSCAN I get the message that I cann't run the
>program in a WINOS2 session.....


WSCAN shells to DOS, which is something that WINOS2 does not directly support.
I believe instructions for tweaking WINOS2 to allow this can be found in
comp.sys.os2.* FAQ list.

SCAN for OS/2 is finishing up its beta-test period and should be available
in 1-2 weeks.  In the meantime, try running the DOS version VIRUSCAN (SCAN).
You'll need to use the /UNATTEND switch to tell it to skip over the hidden
system files on your boot drive, else you'll receive an error message from
OS/2 when SCAN attempts to check them.

